SIMPLE: alee
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Alee
<hw>A*lee"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>a-</ets> + <ets>lee</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>On or
toward the lee, or the side away from the wind; the opposite of
<xex>aweather</xex>. The helm of a ship is <xex>alee</xex> when pressed
close to the lee side.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Hard alee</b></col>, or <col><b>Luff
alee</b></col></mcol>, <cd>an order to put the helm to the lee
side.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Alegar</ent>⟦br⟧
